<div id="databaseWrapper"><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Cell Biology and Development</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Allada, Ravi " src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=14347.jpg&amp;dept=wcas"><div class="title core"><p>Ravi  Allada, MD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Weinberg College of Arts and Sciences and Pathology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Research is focused on the circadian regulation of sleep behavior using the fruit fly Drosophila and incorporates a variety of approaches including biochemistry, molecular biology, genetics, cell culture, electrophysiology, anatomy, and behavior.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header visual_processing"><div>Visual Processing</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Baker, James " src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=10385.jpg&amp;dept=physiology"><div class="title core"><p>James  Baker, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Physiology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Studies of vestibular and visual sensory systems and the reflex motor outputs to the eyes, neck, and limbs.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header visual_processing"><div>Visual Processing</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Cang, Jianhua" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/blank-headshot-160-200.jpg"><div class="title core"><p>Jianhua Cang, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Associate Professor of Neurobiology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">By integrating in vivo electrophysiology, functional imaging, genetics, behavioral and computational approaches, the laboratory studies the neural basis of activity-dependent development in the mouse visual system.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Cell Biology and Development</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Carthew, Richard" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/carthew-160-200.jpg"><div class="title core"><p>Richard Carthew, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Owen L. Coon Professor of Molecular Biosciences</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">The laboratory is interested in understanding how microRNAs specifically inhibit their target genes and the biological consequences of this regulation. The laboratory works on function of microRNAs to promote the differentiation of photoreceptor neurons in the fruit fly, Drosophila.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Circuitry and Function</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="DeVries, Steven H" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=10692.jpg&amp;dept=ophthalmology"><div class="title core"><p>Steven H DeVries, MD, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Ophthalmology and Physiology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">How visual information is processed by local networks of retinal neurons, and synaptic transmission.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Degenerations and Diabetic Retinopathy</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Fawzi, Amani A" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=23979.jpg&amp;dept=ophthalmology"><div class="title core"><p>Amani A Fawzi, MD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Ophthalmology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Translational approaches to age related macular degeneration and ischemic retinal diseases with a special focus on functional retinal imaging and image-guided interventions.
</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header visual_processing"><div>Visual Processing</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Ferster, David" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/ferster-david-160-200.jpg"><div class="title core"><p>David Ferster, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Neurobiology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">The laboratory is studying the neuronal mechanisms by which visual cortex performs transformation of information from the eye. Neuronal connections are traced within the cortex and their functions observed during normal vision by recording intracellularly from neurons in vivo using a patch recording method developed in the lab.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header visual_processing"><div>Visual Processing</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Franconeri, Steven" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/franconeri-steven-160-200.png"><div class="title core"><p>Steven Franconeri, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Associate Professor of Psychology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">The laboratory explores how the visual system transforms a raw image into objects and relations, and why our visual system encounters limitations in how many things we can process at once.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Degenerations and Diabetic Retinopathy</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Henkin, Jack" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/jack-henkin-160-200.jpg"><div class="title core"><p>Jack Henkin, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Senior Translational Fellow,&nbsp;Research Professor,&nbsp;Center for Developmental Therapeutics,&nbsp;Department of Chemistry</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Current research is focused angiogenesis with emphasis on ameliorating neovascular diseases of the retina and the female reproductive system. </div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header glaucoma"><div>Glaucoma</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Johnson, Mark" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/johnson-mark-160-200.jpg"><div class="title core"><p>Mark Johnson, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Biomedical Engineering,&nbsp;Professor of Ophthalmology, Feinberg School of Medicine</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Cellular mechanics and the hydrodynamics of glaucoma; the role of lipids in AMD; transport through connective tissues; esophageal transport; and chaos and diffusion.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header visual_processing"><div>Visual Processing</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Kath, William" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/kath-william-160-200.jpg"><div class="title core"><p>William Kath, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Engineering Sciences and Applied Mathematics and (by courtesy) Neurobiology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Development of computational models of the neural circuitry of the mammalian retina that links the pathways responsible for night and daylight vision.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header glaucoma"><div>Glaucoma</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Knepper, Paul A" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=11792.JPG&amp;dept=ophthalmology"><div class="title core"><p>Paul A Knepper, MD</p><p class="deadline title">Associate Professor of Ophthalmology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Research focuses on the cause, treatment and prevention of glaucoma and Alzheimer's disease. The laboratory specializes in discovering biomarkers of these disease processes.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Cell Biology and Development</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Laurie, Nikia A" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=18473.jpg&amp;dept=pediatrics"><div class="title core"><p>Nikia A Laurie, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Assistant Professor of Pediatrics</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">The laboratory mission is to understand the molecular mechanisms associated with retinoblastoma progression in order to facilitate the identification of novel therapeutic targets.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header cornea"><div>Cornea</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Lavker, Robert M" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=15002.JPG&amp;dept=dermatology"><div class="title core"><p>Robert M Lavker, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Dermatology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">The laboratory focuses on the biology of epithelial stem cells and the cornea, and the roles of microRNAs (miRNAs) in regulating corneal homeostasis.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Degenerations and Diabetic Retinopathy</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Linsenmeier, Robert" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/linsenmeier-robert-160-200.jpg"><div class="title core"><p>Robert Linsenmeier, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Biomedical Engineering,&nbsp;Professor of Neurobiology,&nbsp;Professor of Ophthalmology,&nbsp;Director of Northwestern Center for Engineering Education Research</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">The microenvironment of the mammalian retina, including oxygen and pH regulation in health and disease; engineering education research.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Cell Biology and Development</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Listernick, Robert H" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=12061.jpg&amp;dept=pediatrics"><div class="title core"><p>Robert H Listernick, MD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Pediatrics (Academic General Pediatrics and Primary Care)</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Natural history and treatment of optic pathway tumors in children with neurofibromatosis-1.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Degenerations and Diabetic Retinopathy</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Liu, Kiang J" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=12064.png&amp;dept=prevmed"><div class="title core"><p>Kiang J Liu, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor Emeritus of Preventive Medicine (Epidemiology)</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Multiethnic study of atherosclerosis.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Degenerations and Diabetic Retinopathy</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Molitch, Mark E" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=12571.jpg&amp;dept=med-endo"><div class="title core"><p>Mark E Molitch, MD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Medicine (Endocrinology)</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Pathogenesis and treatment of pituitary tumors and treatment of diabetic complications.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Cell Biology and Development</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Quaggin, Susan E" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=26269.jpg&amp;dept=med-neph"><div class="title core"><p>Susan E Quaggin, MD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Medicine (Nephrology and Hypertension)</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">The major research focus is on the genetic and molecular pathways that establish and maintain complex capillary structures, particularly those forming the renal glomerular filtration barrier. Other interests include the mechanisms of angiogenesis and neovascularization in the retina.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Cell Biology and Development</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Sarthy, Vijay " src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=15849.jpg&amp;dept=ophthalmology"><div class="title core"><p>Vijay  Sarthy, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Ophthalmology and Cell and Molecular Biology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Neuron-glia interactions in the retina; Roles of MÃ¼ller (glia) cells in the pathogenesis of retinal degenerations and diabetic retinopathy.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Circuitry and Function</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Schwartz, Gregory W" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=28472.jpg&amp;dept=ophthalmology"><div class="title core"><p>Gregory W Schwartz, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Assistant Professor of Ophthalmology, Physiology and Weinberg College of Arts and Sciences</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">The research program in computational neuroscience and systems neurophysiology relates to our understanding of how ganglion cells respond to various light stimuli.  In addition, the laboratory studies the visual processing circuits in the inner synaptic layer of the retina.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header visual_processing"><div>Visual Processing</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Segraves, Mark" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/segraves-160-200.jpg"><div class="title core"><p>Mark Segraves, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Associate Professor of Neurobiology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">The laboratory uses the eye movement system as a model for how the brain of primates, including man, controls a variety of movements. Research work focuses upon areas of the rhesus monkey's prefrontal cortex and midbrain that help to control eye movements.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Degenerations and Diabetic Retinopathy</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Starren, Justin B" src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=20839.jpg&amp;dept=prevmed-bioinform"><div class="title core"><p>Justin B Starren, MD, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Preventive Medicine (Health and Biomedical Informatics) and Medical Social Sciences</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Development of intuitive, novel Human Computer Interfaces for healthcare.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header visual_processing"><div>Visual Processing</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Suzuki, Satoro" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/suzuki-satoru-160x200.png"><div class="title core"><p>Satoro Suzuki, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Professor of Psychology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">A major goal of the research is to understand the cortical mechanisms that enable people to perceive coherent global forms from retinal illumination patterns that are often ambiguous as to what meaningful forms and configurations are present.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header glaucoma"><div>Glaucoma</div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Troy, John B." src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/troy-john-160-200.jpg"><div class="title core"><p>John Troy, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Chair and Professor of Biomedical Engineering,&nbsp;Professor of Ophthalmology, Feinberg School of Medicine</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Processing and analysis of images by the mammalian visual system; functional circuitry of the retina; signal theory applied to visual physiology; light adaptation; neural coding; visual prostheses; electrode technology for neural recording and stimulation; glaucoma.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Functional Imaging</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Zhang, Hao" src="https://feinberg-dev.fsm.northwestern.edu/sites/ophthalmology-new/images/non-fsm-profile-pics/zhang-hao-160-200.jpg"><div class="title core"><p>Hao Zhang, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Assistant Professor of Biomedical Engineering,&nbsp;Assistant Professor of Ophthalmology, Feinberg School of Medicine</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">Novel optical imaging technologies for ophthalmic application.</div></div></div></div><div class="card"><div class="header retina"><div>Retina<br><span class="subType">Circuitry and Function</span></div></div><div class="cardContent"><img alt="Zhu, Yongling " src="//fsmweb.northwestern.edu/faculty/shared/load_image.cfm?imageFileName=24979.jpg&amp;dept=ophthalmology"><div class="title core"><p>Yongling  Zhu, PhD</p><p class="deadline title">Assistant Professor of Ophthalmology and Physiology</p></div><div class="focus core"><label>Description</label><div class="desc_full">The laboratory studies the structure and function of genetically isolated retina circuits with anatomical, physiological and imaging tools.</div></div></div></div></div>